@title Trails Through the Archive
@subtitle Four paths through the same landscape, each starting from a different question.
@status draft1
@date 2026-04-13
@category knowledge
@related 000

@argument
Nine guided reading paths through the same landscape — every idea pod in the archive appears on at least one trail, with pod 003 as the gravitational center where multiple trails converge.

@section(surface)

There is no single right order to read these pods. But some readers prefer to be led rather than explore. Here are nine trails through the archive, each starting from a different question and converging on shared territory.

### 1. The Epistemology Trail

*How do we know what we know — and what are we getting wrong right now?*

@link(001) → @link(027) → @link(021) → @link(002) → @link(007) → @link(008) → @link(003) → @link(011) → @link(009) → @link(012) → @link(034) → @link(006) → @link(022) → @link(025) → @link(016) → @link(073)

### 2. The Sensation Trail

*What does direct experience tell us about the structure of reality?*

@link(008) → @link(030) → @link(038) → @link(041) → @link(035) → @link(033) → @link(034) → @link(003) → @link(069)

### 3. The Cosmic Trail

*What is the universe, and where do we fit in it?*

@link(002) → @link(007) → @link(029) → @link(028) → @link(032) → @link(036) → @link(009) → @link(011) → @link(003)

### 4. The AI Trail

*The urgent contemporary question: what have we built, and what do we owe it?*

@link(001) → @link(021) → @link(006) → @link(015) → @link(016) → @link(017) → @link(025) → @link(022) → @link(073) → @link(047) → @link(065)

### 5. The Frameworks Trail

*How do ideas take hold — and what gets lost when they change?*

@link(019) → @link(018) → @link(023) → @link(026) → @link(010) → @link(020) → @link(074) → @link(079)

### 6. The Perception Trail

*How does the nervous system build experience from vibration?*

@link(076) → @link(042) → @link(044) → @link(041) → @link(070) → @link(040) → @link(071) → @link(072) → @link(069)

### 7. The Boundary Trail

*Where does inside meet outside — and what is the boundary made of?*

@link(031) → @link(068) → @link(067) → @link(051) → @link(037) → @link(078) → @link(004) → @link(024) → @link(013)

### 8. The Process Trail

*How does complexity build itself — from physics through biology to mind?*

@link(005) → @link(046) → @link(045) → @link(014) → @link(077) → @link(066) → @link(059) → @link(058) → @link(050) → @link(049) → @link(048)

### 9. The Fractal Trail

*What does one rule, iterated, actually produce?*

@link(052) → @link(054) → @link(062) → @link(064) → @link(060) → @link(056) → @link(057) → @link(053) → @link(063) → @link(061)

@section(depth)

Every idea pod in the archive appears on at least one trail. @link(003) remains the gravitational center — it appears as a destination on the Epistemology, Sensation, and Cosmic trails, marking where the archive's investigations converge on the claim that experience may be fundamental rather than late. The five new trails — Frameworks, Perception, Boundary, Process, and Mandelbrot — cover the remaining pods, tracing how ideas spread and dissolve, how senses build experience from vibration, where inside meets outside, how complexity builds itself, and what one rule iterated actually produces. The @link(000) offers the explorer's approach. These trails offer the pilgrim's.

