messages.content:
That's because the `nav` field controls the top-level nav bar, but Trails is also in `list_menu` where it's near the bottom. Let me move it to the top of the list_menu:

<<<EDIT
target: config/settings.json
mode: patch
---
find:
  "list_menu" : [
    {
      "link" : "list",
      "name" : "Index"
    },
    {
      "link" : "bibliography",
      "name" : "Bibliography"
    },
    {
      "link" : "glossary",
      "name" : "Glossary"
    },
    {
      "link" : "map",
      "name" : "Map"
    },
    {
      "link" : "trails",
      "name" : "Trails"
    },
    {
      "link" : "more",
      "name" : "More"
    }
  ],
~~~
replace:
  "list_menu" : [
    {
      "link" : "trails",
      "name" : "Trails"
    },
    {
      "link" : "list",
      "name" : "Index"
    },
    {
      "link" : "bibliography",
      "name" : "Bibliography"
    },
    {
      "link" : "glossary",
      "name" : "Glossary"
    },
    {
      "link" : "map",
      "name" : "Map"
    },
    {
      "link" : "more",
      "name" : "More"
    }
  ],
>>>

