messages.content:
Good — now I can see the problem. The markdown renderer is wrapping each `<li>` content in `<p>` tags (`<li><p>...</p></li>`), which adds extra spacing. That's because of blank lines between list items in the source. Also, the `<div class="trails-list" markdown="1">` is being passed through literally — the build doesn't process the `markdown="1"` attribute, but the div itself is there and the CSS class works.

The fix is two parts: tighten the CSS to eliminate the paragraph spacing inside list items, and increase the indent. Let me look at the `h2` to figure out the right indent alignment.

<<<EDIT
target: config/site.css
mode: patch
---
find:
/* Trails page: compact bullet lists */
.trails-list ul{margin-left:2rem;margin-bottom:.5rem}
.trails-list li{font-size:.95rem;line-height:1.3;margin-bottom:.1rem}
~~~
replace:
/* Trails page: compact bullet lists */
.trails-list ul{margin-left:2.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem}
.trails-list li{font-size:.95rem;line-height:1.4;margin-bottom:0;padding:0}
.trails-list li p{margin:0;padding:0;line-height:1.4}
>>>

That should kill the extra space — the `<p>` inside each `<li>` was adding margins. The `2.5rem` indent should roughly align the bullets with the text after the numbers in the `## 1.` headings. Take a look and let me know if it needs more or less indent.

