.mobile-sim .wrap--list{margin-left:1.5rem;margin-right:1.5rem}
.mobile-sim .section-tabs-inner{padding:.25rem 1.5rem .25rem .75rem}
.mobile-sim .nav-logo{font-size:.62rem;line-height:1.15;margin-left:0;padding-left:0}
.mobile-sim .nav-links .nav-link-item{display:none}
.mobile-sim .nav-hamburger-btn{display:block}
.mobile-sim .nav-row{position:relative}
.mobile-sim nav{position:relative}
.mobile-sim .section-tab{font-size:.70rem;letter-spacing:.05em;padding:.25rem .25rem}
.mobile-sim .section-tabs-prev,.mobile-sim .section-tabs-next{font-size:.85rem;padding:.25rem .1rem}
.mobile-sim .search-dialog-input{font-size:16px}

messages.content:
The `<p>` tags inside the `<li>` elements are the culprit — even with `margin:0`, the browser may be adding padding or the `<li>` itself has spacing from the `.page-body li` rule. Let me check — the general `.page-body li` has `margin-bottom:.4rem`. That's overriding my `.trails-list li` rule if specificity is lower.

<<<EDIT
target: config/site.css
mode: patch
---
find:
/* Trails page: compact bullet lists */
.trails-list ul{margin-left:2.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem}
.trails-list li{font-size:.95rem;line-height:1.4;margin-bottom:0;padding:0}
.trails-list li p{margin:0;padding:0;line-height:1.4}
~~~
replace:
/* Trails page: compact bullet lists */
.trails-list ul{margin-left:2.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem}
.page-body .trails-list li{font-size:.95rem;line-height:1.3;margin-bottom:0;padding:0}
.page-body .trails-list li p{margin:0;padding:0;line-height:1.3}
>>>

Bumped the specificity so it overrides `.page-body li` and tightened line-height a touch more.

